OL,5,CCouncil bin strike continues
OL,7,FResidents are being advised to present
OL,8,Fboth their recycling and household bin
OL,9,Fon non-strike days when one will be
OL,10,Fcollected, which the council say will
OL,11,Fhelp to minimise disruption.
OL,13,FThere have been more slots added at
OL,14,FMiddlefields Recycling Village,
OL,15,Fhowever as of Tuesday afternoon, the
OL,16,Ffirst available slot was on Monday 29
OL,17,FJanuary.
OL,19,FThe refuse service supports 72,000
OL,20,Fhouseholds across South Tyneside,
OL,21,Femptying 6.2 million bins every year.
